## â™¿ ACCESSIBILITY (WCAG AA Standard)

### Color Contrast
```
âœ… Text on background: 4.5:1 ratio minimum
âœ… Disabled elements: OK if <3:1 (they're disabled)
âœ… Test with: WebAIM Contrast Checker
âœ… Don't rely on color alone (use text labels, icons)
```

### Keyboard Navigation
```
âœ… Tab through all interactive elements
âœ… Enter to activate buttons/links
âœ… Space to activate checkboxes/radio buttons
âœ… Escape to close modals/popovers
âœ… Arrow keys for menus/dropdowns
âœ… Focus visible (outline on :focus-visible)
```

### Screen Readers (ARIA)
```
âœ… <button> has aria-label if no text
âœ… <img> has alt text (or role="presentation" if decorative)
âœ… Form inputs have <label>
âœ… Modals have role="dialog" + aria-modal="true"
âœ… Live regions have aria-live="polite" or aria-live="assertive"
âœ… Icon buttons have aria-label (e.g., aria-label="Close menu")
```

### Semantic HTML
```
âœ… <header> for top navigation
âœ… <nav> for navigation areas
âœ… <main> for main content
âœ… <article> for standalone content
âœ… <aside> for sidebars
âœ… <footer> for footer
âœ… <section> for logical sections
âœ… Heading hierarchy: h1 > h2 > h3 (no skipping)
```

